frameDefinitions: An Item is detached from a Source, or Items are detached from each other.
An Entity changes from a Prior_state to a Post_state in a sequence that follows a pre-defined plan, expectation, or model of change.
A physical entity, construed as a point-Sound_source, emits a Sound.
An Agent makes a particular facial expression, generally in response to some Internal_cause (generally an emotional state).
The words in this frame refer to facial Expressions and the Possessors of those Expressions.
A perceptible Figure shows up against a Ground location due to Light shining on/from it, its salience possibly dependent on a Cause_of_shine.
frameExamples: When the snow plow is <t>disconnected</t> from the vehicle, extend the lift cylinder to the end of its stroke and coat the chrome rod with a light grease.
Their offensive armament has <t>developed</t> from short range missiles to long-range ballistic weaponry in a relatively short period .
His eyes <t>smile</t>, but his lips do not.
listRoleDefinitions: <fen>Item</fen> identifies the entity that is detached from a <fen>Source</fen>.
<fen>Items</fen> identifies the plural items that are detached from each other.
<fen>Source</fen> identifies the location from which the <fen>Item</fen>(s) is detached.
The object that undergoes change.
The time at which the progress occurs.
The location where the Progress occurs.

The frame element <fen>Sound_source</fen> is assigned to a constituent referring to a physical entity which emits a sound. Such an entity must have an appropriately complex internal structure such that it can create a sound. For example, a machine or some other thing with moving parts can create sound by itself.

The frame element <fen>Sound</fen> is incorporated in the meaning of the verbs of this frame. Otherwise, this role is assigned to NPs which actually refer to a sound in the presence of the target. This typically occurs when the target is a verb used as a modifier in its <ment>-ing</ment> form, e.g.:
An event in which one or more <fen>Sound_source</fen>s participate and which is accompanied by <fen>Sound</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Noisy_event</fen> occurs.

The location of the <fen>Sound_source</fen>. This role differs from <fen>Location_of_source</fen> only in terms of point of view; the latter role implies a point of view that is not on the <fen>Sound_source</fen>.
The individual that assumes a particular facial expression.
The particular part of the face that the <fen>Agent</fen> moves into a facial expression.
The point in time at which the change in facial_expression takes place.
This is the <fen>Expression</fen> made.
This is the person who exhibitis the <fen>Expression</fen>.
The emotion that is conveyed by a particular <fen>Expression</fen>.
The percept which is perceived at a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location.
The location of the phenomenon.
The <fen>Light</fen> which is emitted.  In this frame, it is usually incorporated in verbs and adjectives, and is the denotation of many of the nouns.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Figure</fen> is observed against the <fen>Ground</fen> location due to <fen>Light</fen> shining on it.
The spatial setting in which the <fen>Figure</fen> shows up against a <fen>Ground</fen> location.
listRoleExamples: I feel like <fex>my head</fex> is detached from the rest of my body.
<fex>The neck vertebrae</fex> are unfused in rorquals and gray whales, which allows for some flexibility at the head and neck.
The toilet is loose <fex>from the floor</fex> and must be repaired.
Advances <fex>in marketing techniques</fex> have since rendered it obsolete.
<fex>When</fex> did the X-wing progress beyond the drawing board?
It's going to beep again <fex>in two minutes</fex>.
Hot coals glowed <fex>behind the fire grate</fex>.
<fex>In the morning</fex> the grass glistened with dew
<fex>Outside</fex> something was shimmering on the shore.
